<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><!DOCTYPE topic  PUBLIC '-//OASIS//DTD DITA Topic//EN'  'topic.dtd'><topic id="GUID_65007FDF-3554-48B8-92EB-C5CDC57276E0"><title>Type-C TBT+USB+DP 40G Retimer Topology</title><body><section id="SECTION_E6B176DC-A80E-45E7-A279-B3D0EB37586A"><fig id="FIG_type-c_tbt_usb_dp_40g_retimer_topology_diagram_1"><title>Type-C TBT+USB+DP 40G Retimer Topology Diagram</title><image href="FIG_type-c tbt+usb+dp 40g retimer topology diagram_1.png" scalefit="yes" id="IMG_type-c_tbt_usb_dp_40g_retimer_topology_diagram_1_png" /></fig><table id="TABLE_E6B176DC-A80E-45E7-A279-B3D0EB37586A_1"><title>Type-C TBT+USB+DP 40G Retimer Topology Notes</title><tgroup cols="2"><thead><row><entry>Note</entry><entry>Detail</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>Number of vias allowed</p></entry><entry><p>2 before retimer, 2 after retimer.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Maximum via stub length</p></entry><entry><p>250 um per via between CPU and retimer. Retimer post-channel cannot have via stub.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Routing style</p></entry><entry><p>Microstrip main route routing must be interleaved.</p><p>To reduce system RFI/ EMI, it is recommended to use SL instead of MS. If MS routing is needed, refer to EMC PDG for RFI/ EMI mitigation.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Reference plane for microstrip route</p></entry><entry><p>Must be continuous ground.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Reference plane for stripline route</p></entry><entry><p>Ground on both sides strongly preferred. If necessary, one side can be a IO rail power plane with Iccmax &lt; 5A that has low amount of low frequency noise, but the other side must be continuous ground.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Reference plane for dual stripline route</p></entry><entry><p>Ground on both sides strongly preferred. If necessary, one side can be a IO rail power plane with Iccmax &lt; 5A that has low amount of low frequency noise, but the other side must be continuous ground and it is the layer that is closer to the signal route.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>ESD</p></entry><entry><p>On-Semi ESDL2012 or ESDL2013.</p><p>Alternative option: Semtech RClamp1011ZC.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>AC cap value</p></entry><entry><p>135 nF to 265 nF including tolerance.</p><p /><p>For the post-channel cap</p><p>- Form factor: 0201 recommended.</p><p>- Rated voltage: 25 V.</p><p /><p>For the pre-channel cap</p><p>- Form factor: 0201 recommended.</p><p>- Rated voltage: 6.3 V.</p><p /></entry></row><row><entry><p>Crx cap value</p></entry><entry><p>297 nF to 363 nF including tolerance.</p><p>- Form factor: 0201 recommended.</p><p>- Rated voltage: 25 V.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Rb resistor value</p></entry><entry><p>220 kΩ ± 5%</p><p>Form factor: 0201 recommended.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Rc resistor value</p></entry><entry><p>1 Ω ± 10%</p><p>- Form factor: 0201 recommended.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>TX bleed resistor placeholder</p></entry><entry><p>Recommend having a placeholder for an 0201 Rb resistor between the AC cap and Type-C connector on the SSTX pairs.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Retimer</p></entry><entry><p>Hayden Bridge and Gothic Bridge</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Total insertion loss budget from CPU pins to retimer pins</p></entry><entry><p>17 dB @ 10 GHz. Inclusive of HVM variation.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Total insertion loss budget from retimer pins to Type-C connector pads</p></entry><entry><p>4.5 dB @ 10 GHz on PCB. Inclusive of HVM variation.  Not inclusive of connector.</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Supported interfaces</p></entry><entry><p>Thunderbolt 4.0, USB3.2 Gen2x2, USB4.0 Gen3 and DP2.1 (UHBR20).</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Fiberweave</p></entry><entry><p>Must adhere to fiberweave related best routing practices (#406926).</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table id="TABLE_E6B176DC-A80E-45E7-A279-B3D0EB37586A_2"><title>Max Number of vias</title><tgroup cols="3"><thead><row><entry>Signal Group</entry><entry>Max Number of Vias Allowed</entry><entry>Via Placement</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>Rx, Tx</p></entry><entry><p>2</p></entry><entry><p>Pre-Channel</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>Rx, Tx</p></entry><entry><p>2</p></entry><entry><p>Post-Channel</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_AC73201F-8636-4D94-A49C-636A2F014D6D"><title>Mainstream, Rx,Tx, Post-Channel</title><table id="TABLE_AC73201F-8636-4D94-A49C-636A2F014D6D_1"><title>Type-C TBT+USB+DP 40G Retimer Topology Mainstream, Rx,Tx, Post-Channel Routing Guidelines</title><tgroup cols="3"><thead><row><entry>Segment</entry><entry>Tline Type</entry><entry>Max Length Segment (mm)</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>M3+M4+M5</p></entry><entry><p>DSL, MS, SL</p></entry><entry><p>33</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p>Max Length Total (mm): 33</p></section><section id="SECTION_FD223734-A0F4-4723-A0F8-C270640F0360"><title>Mainstream, Rx,Tx, Pre-Channel</title><table id="TABLE_FD223734-A0F4-4723-A0F8-C270640F0360_1"><title>Type-C TBT+USB+DP 40G Retimer Topology Mainstream, Rx,Tx, Pre-Channel Routing Guidelines</title><tgroup cols="3"><thead><row><entry>Segment</entry><entry>Tline Type</entry><entry>Max Length Segment (mm)</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>BO</p></entry><entry><p>DSL, MS, SL</p></entry><entry><p>8</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>M1+M2</p></entry><entry><p>DSL, MS, SL</p></entry><entry><p>192</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p>Max Length Total (mm): 200</p><p>Max Length Total Note: Max length can be increased up to 220mm (M1+M2 = 212mm), if more than 90% of the routed as stripline with premium mid-loss (PML) material.</p></section><section id="SECTION_7578F3DE-69B7-42C8-9202-270A92086D0A"><title>Thin PCB, Rx,Tx, Post-Channel</title><table id="TABLE_7578F3DE-69B7-42C8-9202-270A92086D0A_1"><title>Type-C TBT+USB+DP 40G Retimer Topology Thin PCB, Rx,Tx, Post-Channel Routing Guidelines</title><tgroup cols="3"><thead><row><entry>Segment</entry><entry>Tline Type</entry><entry>Max Length Segment (mm)</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>M3+M4+M5</p></entry><entry><p>DSL, MS, SL</p></entry><entry><p>33</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p>Max Length Total (mm): 33</p></section><section id="SECTION_265D03BE-011E-4669-9F86-74DBF0C987B2"><title>Thin PCB, Rx,Tx, Pre-Channel</title><table id="TABLE_265D03BE-011E-4669-9F86-74DBF0C987B2_1"><title>Type-C TBT+USB+DP 40G Retimer Topology Thin PCB, Rx,Tx, Pre-Channel Routing Guidelines</title><tgroup cols="3"><thead><row><entry>Segment</entry><entry>Tline Type</entry><entry>Max Length Segment (mm)</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>BO</p></entry><entry><p>DSL, MS, SL</p></entry><entry><p>8</p></entry></row><row><entry><p>M1+M2</p></entry><entry><p>DSL, MS, SL</p></entry><entry><p>192</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p>Max Length Total (mm): 200</p><p>Max Length Total Note: Max length can be increased up to 220mm (M1+M2 = 212mm), if more than 90% of the routed as stripline with premium mid-loss (PML) material.</p></section></body></topic>